cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.LG

The paper deals with the detection of radical content over online media using deep learning algorithms. This involves natural language processing and classification of text data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also deals with the security aspect of online media, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of deep learning algorithms for classification could also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper involves data collection and annotation, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
